The following text was copied from http://www.praxiom.com/iso-14001-intro.htm (see our first paragraph) 
to http://www.explorandes.com/Awards (see right column top of page):

“ISO 14001 2004 is an environmental management standard. It specifies a set of environmental management requirements for environmental management systems. The purpose of this standard is to help all types of organizations to protect the environment, to prevent pollution, and to improve their environmental performance.”
